31class RtcEventGenericAckReceived final : public RtcEvent {
32 public:
33 static constexpr Type kType = Type::GenericAckReceived;
34
35 // For a collection of acked packets, it creates a vector of logs to log with
36 // the same timestamp.
37 static std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtcEventGenericAckReceived>> CreateLogs(
38 int64_t packet_number,
39 const std::vector<AckedPacket>& acked_packets);
40
41 ~RtcEventGenericAckReceived() override;
42
43 std::unique_ptr<RtcEventGenericAckReceived> Copy() const;
44
45 Type GetType() const override { return kType; }
46 bool IsConfigEvent() const override { return false; }
47
48 // An identifier of the packet which contained an ack.
49 int64_t packet_number() const { return packet_number_; }
50
51 // An identifier of the acked packet.
52 int64_t acked_packet_number() const { return acked_packet_number_; }
53
54 // Timestamp when the |acked_packet_number| was received by the remote side.
55 absl::optional<int64_t> receive_acked_packet_time_ms() const {
56 return receive_acked_packet_time_ms_;
57 }
58
59 private:
60 RtcEventGenericAckReceived(const RtcEventGenericAckReceived& packet);
61
62 // When the ack is received, |packet_number| identifies the packet which
63 // contained an ack for |acked_packet_number|, and contains the
64 // |receive_acked_packet_time_ms| on which the |acked_packet_number| was
65 // received on the remote side. The |receive_acked_packet_time_ms| may be
66 // null.
67 RtcEventGenericAckReceived(
68 int64_t timestamp_us,
69 int64_t packet_number,
70 int64_t acked_packet_number,
71 absl::optional<int64_t> receive_acked_packet_time_ms);
72
73 const int64_t packet_number_;
74 const int64_t acked_packet_number_;
75 const absl::optional<int64_t> receive_acked_packet_time_ms_;
76};
